	(text_box "Diff Input Stage. In- has 60Hz hum return path. Input Gain of about 1/2 to start attenuation. Need to keep max of 10mVpp input at LM13700. Extensive source testing with done at max Preamp level on different records to ensure that is the case. Keeping Jonhnson noise and 1/f noise down with 47 ohm and 47nF cap. LM13700 output is current, and with 51K on NE5532 this is still down around 6dB from the original signal but very usable. Ctrl is current based and is split between the two resistors to help keep it better balanced. Not using diode bias here, in my bench tests 2nd harmonic distortion increased significantly and with signal this low it isn't needed."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 121.92 76.2 0)
		(size 50.8 41.91)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
